The Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) last week announced the appointed of Dr Isa Abdulmumin as the Acting Director, Corporate Communications Department. He takes over from Mr Osita Nwanisobi, who has retired from the apex bank. Until his appointment, Dr Abdulmumin was a Deputy Director in the Corporate Communications Department. According to the apex bank, Dr Abdulmumin has been a dedicated CBN staff member for several years and is reputed to be a hardworking, go-getter, efficient professional and a media personality. US extends tourist visa validity for Nigerians to 5yrs Early lessons of voter polarisation and INEC as votes are being counted Dr Abdulmumin appointment is coming at a time that the bank is driving several initiative like the redesigned naira notes, the eNaira as well as  the various  intervention schemes in its bid to ensure businesses across all sectors of the economy receive support. He comes to the job with several years of experience in Business reporting and strategic marketing communication as well of several high level local and international training.